728680f-a.text:
(1)
Chelsea Road, north side, east of Spencer Street (point of vantage), showing the W.F. Carey house and barn (1853-1874). It was later the Wm. T. Meredith property (1898-1917). The house is about 400 feet back of the road. In the far background is visible
Goethals Bridge.
May 4, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, at a later date.
May 16, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
728680f-a.folder: Chelsea Road & Spencer Road, Staten Island, NY

729682f-a.text:
Spencer Street, west from Chelsea Road toward Arthur Kill. The vessels tied up in the Kill are old United States Shipping Board boats.
May 16, 1937
P. L. Sperr
